article_title: Stuck in the Middle With Hillary
article_text: Stuart Varney: This week on ”The Journal Editorial Report,” Hillary Clinton is off and running to the left, promising to take up the cause of everyday Americans and taking shots at hedge-fund managers and CEOs. Is she a credible champion for the middle class? Plus, Marco Rubio joins what is shaping up to be a crowded Republican field, declaring that yesterday is over. So is he the face of the GOP’s future?And the White House pulls its veto threat as an Iran vote moves to the full Senate. Did President Obama blink? Does he have...
